    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cheney for Vice President? Some Early Reviews</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter J Bauer letter disputes July 26 news analysis of Gov George W Bush choice of Richard B Cheney as running mate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Safe Pick Is Revealing'' (news analysis, front page, July 26):</p>
        <p>You say Dick Cheney, George W. Bush's choice for his running mate,  brings ''few obvious political advantages to the ticket.'' I disagree. Mr. Cheney brings the most important of all political advantages to the Republican ticket: credibility.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Safe Pick Is Revealing'' (news analysis, front page, July 26):</p>
        <p>You say Dick Cheney, George W. Bush's choice for his running mate,  brings ''few obvious political advantages to the ticket.'' I disagree. Mr. Cheney brings the most important of all political advantages to the Republican ticket: credibility.</p>
        <p>Rather than some governor with no international experience being paired with, for example, another governor with no international experience, Mr. Bush has chosen an experienced, knowledgeable running mate.</p>
        <p>The selection of Mr. Cheney as the vice-presidential candidate has taken me off the fence. Knowing that Mr. Bush has the good sense to surround himself with capable, experienced people rather than a partner who can bring in a state or several will likely have as big an effect on others, too.</p>
        <p>PETER J. BAUER  Columbus, Ohio, July 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
